# Bit Manipulation Cheat Sheet (Must Remember)

# Left Shift (`<<`) and Right Shift (`>>`) in Java

Bitwise shift operators move bits left or right.

---

# 1. Left Shift (`<<`)

Shifts all bits to the left.

## Formula

```java
n << k = n * (2^k)
```

---

## Example

```java
int n = 5;

System.out.println(n << 1);
```

### Binary Representation

```text
5 = 00000101

5 << 1
= 00001010
= 10
```

### Output

```text
10
```

---

## More Examples

```java
5 << 1 = 10
5 << 2 = 20
5 << 3 = 40
```

---

# 2. Right Shift (`>>`)

Shifts all bits to the right.

## Formula

```java
n >> k = n / (2^k)
```

> Integer division is performed.

---

## Example

```java
int n = 20;

System.out.println(n >> 1);
```

### Binary Representation

```text
20 = 00010100

20 >> 1
= 00001010
= 10
```

### Output

```text
10
```

---

## More Examples

```java
20 >> 1 = 10
20 >> 2 = 5
20 >> 3 = 2
```

---

