# Bit Mask

A Bit Mask is simply:

```java
1 << k
```

Used to access the kth bit.

Examples:

```java
1 << 0 = 0001
1 << 1 = 0010
1 << 2 = 0100
1 << 3 = 1000
```

&  → Check / Clear
|  → Set
^  → Toggle (Flip)
~  → Invert All Bits
# Bitwise Operators — Easy Memory Table

| Operator | Purpose | Memory Trick |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| `&` | Check or Clear a Bit | Keep matching bits |
| `\|` | Set a Bit | Force a bit to `1` |
| `^` | Flip / Toggle a Bit | Change `0↔1` |
| `~` | Flip All Bits | Reverse every bit |

