# Quick Examples

## 1. Check k-th Bit

```java
(n & (1 << k)) != 0
```

Example:

```text
1010
0010
----
0010
```

Result ≠ 0 → Bit is set.

---

## 2. Clear k-th Bit

```java
n & ~(1 << k)
```

Example:

```text
1010
1101
----
1000
```

The k-th bit becomes `0`.

---

## 3. Set k-th Bit

```java
n | (1 << k)
```

Example:

```text
1000
0010
----
1010
```

The k-th bit becomes `1`.

---

## 4. Toggle k-th Bit

```java
n ^ (1 << k)
```

Example:

```text
1010
0010
----
1000
```

The k-th bit changes from `1 → 0`.

If it was `0`, it would become `1`.

---

## 5. Invert All Bits

```java
~n
```

Example:

```text
1010
↓
0101
```

Every bit is flipped.
n ^ (1 << k)   // Toggle k-th bit
~x             // Equals -(x + 1)

~x = -(x + 1)
~3 = -(3 + 1)
   = -4

n ^ (1 << 0) = 3
~(n ^ (1 << 0) ) = -4
